# Keep the docker build context lean and free of files that should
# never reach the daemon. The cache image's Dockerfile uses `COPY . .`
# from the repo root, so anything here is excluded from the tarball
# sent to the daemon (and thus from the build).
#
# Excludes mirror .gitignore where appropriate, plus a few CI/local
# artifacts that .gitignore does not cover (e.g. .codex/ holds review
# tempfiles, .github/ is repo metadata, prompt is a local session
# scratchpad).

# Version control + repo metadata.
.git/
.gitignore
.github/

# Local CI/tooling state.
.codex/
.idea/
.vscode/
.DS_Store

# Local secrets and credentials. The cache image's build stage does
# `COPY . .`, so anything in the repo root that holds secrets would
# end up baked into a build layer (and into the daemon's layer cache)
# even though the runtime stage only copies the compiled binary. Belt
# and braces — these patterns are unlikely to exist in this repo, but
# excluding them is free insurance against future accidents.
.env
.env.*
.netrc
.npmrc
.pypirc
.aws/
.ssh/
*.pem
*.key
*.p12
*.pfx

# Build artifacts (host-side; the in-image build produces fresh ones).
build/
dist/
*.test
*.out
*.deb

# Documentation does not affect the binary.
README.md
SPEC.md
NOTES.md

# Local scratchpad — not part of any image.
prompt

# Note: e2e/ is intentionally NOT excluded. The cache image's runtime
# stage does `COPY e2e/cache.toml`, and .dockerignore filtering applies
# to the build-context tarball itself — excluding e2e/ here would make
# that COPY fail.
